# NAME: Google_Proxy
# AUTHOR: Kevin (kevshen13)
# REPO: https://github.com/kevshen13/surge-rules
# DESCRIPTION: Google and Gmail domains that should be routed through proxy
# UPDATED: 2026-04-04
# MAINTENANCE: Maintain this list by route behavior under the current network.
# RULE: Include Google connectivity, static-resource, and Gmail mail-protocol endpoints that should avoid direct routing in your environment.
# RULE: Keep this list conservative and focused on domains that are known to fail or stall on direct routes.

# ==================== Google connectivity / static ====================
DOMAIN,connectivitycheck.gstatic.com
DOMAIN,ssl.gstatic.com
DOMAIN,www.gstatic.com
DOMAIN,fonts.googleapis.com
DOMAIN,fonts.gstatic.com
DOMAIN-SUFFIX,gstatic.com
DOMAIN-SUFFIX,googleapis.com
DOMAIN-SUFFIX,googleusercontent.com
DOMAIN-SUFFIX,withgoogle.com

# ==================== Gmail mail protocol ====================
DOMAIN,imap.gmail.com
DOMAIN,pop.gmail.com
DOMAIN,smtp.gmail.com
DOMAIN,smtp.googlemail.com
DOMAIN,smtp-relay.gmail.com
DOMAIN-KEYWORD,gmail-smtp
